b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe01123.htm)  [Next](sbe01125.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n[Buy this Book at\nAmazon.com](http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/B002DEMBW6/internetsacredte)\n\n* * *\n\n[![](../../img/tn_hin.jpg)](index.htm)  \n_The Upanishads, Part 1 (SBE01)_ , by Max Muller, [1879], at sacred-texts.com\n\n* * *\n\n### SIXTH KHA _N_ _D_ A.\n\n1\\. 'That which is the subtile portion of curds, when churned, rises upwards,\nand becomes butter.\n\n2\\. 'In the same manner, my child, the subtile portion of earth (food), when\neaten, rises upwards, and becomes mind.\n\n3\\. 'That which is the subtile portion of water, when drunk, rises upwards,\nand becomes breath.\n\n4\\. 'That which is the subtile portion of fire, when consumed, rises upwards,\nand becomes speech.\n\n5\\. 'For mind, my child, comes of earth, breath of water, speech of fire.'\n\n'Please, Sir, inform me still more,' said the son.\n\n'Be it so, my child,' the father replied.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: VI, 7](sbe01125.htm)\n\n"